 {"id":"bd-2e33","title":"Add PromptError::InputTooLong variant","description":"## Task Description

Add a new error variant to PromptError for signaling input length limit exceeded.

## Implementation

### 1. Update PromptError enum (src/interactive.rs, line ~102)

```rust
/// Errors returned by prompt operations.
#[derive(Debug)]
pub enum PromptError {
    /// Prompt requires an interactive console but `Console::is_interactive()` is false.
    NotInteractive,
    /// Input stream reached EOF without yielding a value.
    Eof,
    /// Underlying I/O error.
    IoError(io::Error),
    /// Input validation failed.
    InvalidInput(String),
    /// Input exceeded maximum allowed length.
    InputTooLong {
        /// Maximum allowed input length in bytes
        limit: usize,
        /// Actual input length received (may be approximate if terminated early)
        received: usize,
    },
}
```

### 2. Update Display impl

```rust
impl std::fmt::Display for PromptError {
    fn fmt(&self, f: &mut std::fmt::Formatter<'_>) -> std::fmt::Result {
        match self {
            // ... existing variants ...
            Self::InputTooLong { limit, received } => {
                write!(f, "input too long: received {} bytes, limit is {} bytes", received, limit)
            }
        }
    }
}
```

### 3. Update std::error::Error impl

```rust
impl std::error::Error for PromptError {
    fn source(&self) -> Option<&(dyn std::error::Error + 'static)> {
        match self {
            Self::IoError(e) => Some(e),
            _ => None,  // InputTooLong has no source error
        }
    }
}
```

### 4. Add helper methods

```rust
impl PromptError {
    /// Returns true if this error indicates input was too long.
    pub fn is_input_too_long(&self) -> bool {
        matches!(self, Self::InputTooLong { .. })
    }

    /// Returns the length limit if this is an InputTooLong error.
    pub fn input_limit(&self) -> Option<usize> {
        match self {
            Self::InputTooLong { limit, .. } => Some(*limit),
            _ => None,
        }
    }
}
```

### 5. Add tests

```rust
#[test]
fn test_prompt_error_input_too_long_display() {
    let err = PromptError::InputTooLong { limit: 256, received: 1024 };
    assert_eq!(err.to_string(), "input too long: received 1024 bytes, limit is 256 bytes");
}

#[test]
fn test_prompt_error_input_too_long_helpers() {
    let err = PromptError::InputTooLong { limit: 100, received: 200 };
    assert!(err.is_input_too_long());
    assert_eq!(err.input_limit(), Some(100));

    let other = PromptError::Eof;
    assert!(!other.is_input_too_long());
    assert_eq!(other.input_limit(), None);
}
```

